<subSubSection lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1912,2011]" lastBlockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1912,1939]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Description</emphasis>
. Habitus as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[612,698,1912,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1841,1866]" captionTargetBox="[202,1397,292,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1435,273,1817]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 24. Hydrochus pictus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587231/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Size: 
<typeStatus box="[784,882,1912,1938]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
(length/width, mm): body (length to elytral apices) 2.31/0.86; head width 0.60; pronotum l/w 0.55/0.60; PA 0.60; PB 0.43; elytra 1.38/0.86. Body size small (ca. 
<quantity box="[151,255,1985,2011]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.31" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="2.31">2.31 mm</quantity>
). Dorsum grey, with moderately strong iridescence, elytra with several large black spots. Legs testaceous, with tibiofemoral joints darker. Punctation on elytra ca. 2– 
<date box="[817,843,153,179]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">3x</date>
that of pronotum. Elytra interstriae ca. 1–1.5x strial puncture diameter. Interstria 9 
<superScript attach="left" box="[488,501,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">th</superScript>
more convex than others, overhanging 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[972,985,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">th</superScript>
interstria. Usual area of callus on 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1381,1394,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">th</superScript>
not raised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pronotum slightly wider than long (as ca. 55/60), widest at anterior margin, markedly narrowed at base, sides straight, smooth; anterior margin bisinuate; depressions very shallow, or absent; punctation quite uniform over pronotum</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Elytra with spaces between strial punctures ca. 0.5x their diameter, to narrow ridges; apices rather sharply conjointly rounded in dorsal view, in lateral view outer margin with slight angulation.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,1432,441,467]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ventral characters: Mentum moderately coarsely punctate, median fovea shallow; submentum without foveae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[377,460,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1841,1866]" captionTargetBox="[202,1397,292,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1435,273,1817]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 24. Hydrochus pictus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587231/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) general characters: parameres long, tapering to very fine apices, very narrow and extending well beyond distal end of aedeagus, tips in dorsal/ventral views very thin and sharply pointed, in lateral view tips very thin and arcuate ventrad; basal piece shorter than parameres, in lateral view markedly arcuate, orifice with rim sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,1013,621,647]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Dorsal surface: adtl lacking; pdmm slightly overlapping alm; adbl small.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ventral surface: avtl near basal 1/3 of aedeagus; pvmm overlapping alm, medial margins very narrowly separated.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1093,729,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,1093,729,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,729,755]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in reference to the numerous large black spots of the elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
